HEADWORD: Cheliform
<hw>Chel"i*form</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>chhlh`</grk> claw + <ets>-form</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having a movable joint or finger closing against a preceding joint
or a projecting part of it, so that the whole may be used for grasping,
as the claw of a crab; pincherlike.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

